                <head>87. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>President <persName corresp="#p_FGR_1">Gerald Ford</persName> and Leonid
                        <persName corresp="#p_BLI_1">Brezhnev</persName>, General Secretary of the
                    Communist Party of the Soviet Union, held a summit in Vladivostok November
                    23–24, 1974. The strategic arms limitation talks (SALT II) dominated the agenda.
                    The two leaders opened the summit on November 23 at 2:20 p.m. with discussions
                    about SALT II as well as general U.S.-Soviet relations and the Middle East. They
                    met again at 6:15 p.m. to talk exclusively about SALT II. Memoranda of
                    conversation are in the Ford Library, National Security Adviser, <persName
                        corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName> Discussions on <gloss
                        target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>, Middle East, and China, Box 1, <gloss
                        target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss> Memcons and Reports, November 23–24, 1974,
                    Vladivostok Summit. The memoranda of conversation of all the Vladivostok summit
                    meetings are printed in <ref target="frus1969-76v16">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1969–1976, Volume XVI, Soviet
                        Union, August 1974–December 1976</ref>.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_FGR_1">Ford</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BLI_1"
                        >Brezhnev</persName> held their final SALT II discussion on November 24 from
                    10:10 a.m. to 1:40 p.m. The memorandum of conversation is <ref target="#d88"
                        >Document 88</ref>. After their last meeting, <persName corresp="#p_FGR_1"
                        >Ford</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_BLI_1">Brezhnev</persName>
                    attended a ceremony in the conference hall at Okeanskaya Sanitorium, where they
                    signed a joint communiqué. The two sides also released a joint statement on the
                    limitation of strategic offensive arms. The full text of these two statements is
                    in <hi rend="italic">Public Papers: <persName corresp="#p_FGR_1"
                        >Ford</persName>, 1974</hi>, pages 657–662. <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1"
                        >Kissinger</persName> held a press conference following the ceremony to
                    answers queries about the summit. The transcript of the press confer<pb
                        facs="0410" n="381" xml:id="pg_381"/>ence is in Department of State <hi
                        rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, December 23, 1974, pages 898–905.</p>
